<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="form-v">form <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /fɔːm/    美 /fɔːrm/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(使) 形成；建立；构成：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Ice formed in the river. 
河上结了冰。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>form an opinion / impression</strong>
形成看法/印象</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The United Nations was formed in 1945.
联合国成立于1945年。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Small talk can help people form new friendships.
闲聊能帮助人们建立新的友谊。</p><footer>2015安徽</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Rice forms a large part of Chinese diet.
米饭是中国人饮食中很重要的一部分。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>起...作用；塑造 (性格等)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The trees form a natural protection from the sun's rays.
树木成了遮挡阳光的天然屏障。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Events in early childhood often help to form a child's characters in later life.
童年早期的经历往往影响着孩子日后性格的形成。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We can form a good habit of putting the rubbish in the trash can.
我们要养成把垃圾投进垃圾箱的好习惯。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>formation /fɔː'meɪʃn/ n [U] &amp; [C]  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the formation of good habits
良好习惯的养成</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>One way to understand thousands of new words is to gain a good knowledge of basic word formation.
理解大量新词的一个方法是掌握好基本的构词法。</p></div></div>